# Virtual Environment Requirement

**CRITICAL:** This project MUST use the virtual environment for all Python operations.

## Running Scripts

Always activate the venv before running any Python scripts:

```bash
cd /home/cmf/Work/vmt-dev && source venv/bin/activate && python <script>
```

## Common Commands

```bash
# Run main simulation
source venv/bin/activate && python main.py scenarios/<scenario>.yaml

# Run launcher GUI
source venv/bin/activate && python launcher.py

# Run tests
source venv/bin/activate && pytest

# Run headless simulation
source venv/bin/activate && python scripts/run_headless.py

# View logs
source venv/bin/activate && python view_logs.py
```

## Virtual Environment Details

- **Location:** [venv/](mdc:venv/)
- **Python Version:** 3.11+
- **Dependencies:** [requirements.txt](mdc:requirements.txt)
- **Dev Dependencies:** requirements-dev.txt (if exists)

## Installing Dependencies

```bash
source venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Why This Matters

The venv contains essential dependencies:
- pygame (visualization)
- PyQt6 (GUI launcher)
- numpy (calculations)
- pytest (testing)
- mypy, ruff, black (code quality)

**Never run Python commands without activating venv first!**
